<eventList name="FR_START_WARZONE_LIST">
	<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_COALITION" req="stability" lvl="750" max_lvl="999"/>
	<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_REBEL" req="stability" lvl="500" max_lvl="749"/>
	<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION" req="stability" lvl="250" max_lvl="499"/>
	<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_PIRATE" req="stability" lvl="-999" max_lvl="249"/>
</eventList>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_COALITION">
	<metaVariable name="fr_juke_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<variable name="fr_sec_unique_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_start" global="false">
		<color r="46" g="252" b="51" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>This sector would have once been a safe haven for you and your crew, but ever since the Rebel attack and the sequential Coalition invasion, this sector has become a no man's land. If that wasn't bad enough, pirates have also been drawn into this place hoping to score easy scrap. Watch your step and always be on guard.</text>
	<variable name="loc_unique_sectors" op="add" val="1"/>
	<changeBackground>FR_BACK_SECTOR_WARZONE</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_MFK</customFleet>
	<ship load="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>It appears the Coalition has managed to spare a elite guard ship to keep the sector from getting reinforcements, be they Rebel or Federation. "So you are the reinforcements they sent to try and fight us? That's adorable. Tell me, oh Federation ship that could, how do you expect to stop an endless tide with only a single barricade?" With this, the guard ship's weapons power on.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Prepare for combat!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You lock your weapons onto the guard and move in to attack.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="fr_unique_mantis_queen" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Leikonpliiinakra) Leikonpliiinakra demands free passage!</text>
				<event>
					<text>"How dare you address your Queen in such a way? You will let us pass this instant or be publically excuted at my hands. Am I clear?"
						
					The guard scrambles to attention at the sight of the Queen. "O-Of course, your highness! Right this way!" The guard allows you to pass while also sending some supplies your way and alerting the Coalition fleet to allow you to pass.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="unique_nights" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Nights) Nights demands free passage!</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Lissssten here you poor excusssse for a ssssoldier, you will let ussss passsss or I will make you the Coalition'ssss number 1 enemy!"

					The guard freezes for a moment before powering down their weapons. "Very well, Captain. I will let the fleet know at once." The guard also sends some supplies your way.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="unique_tyrdeo" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Tyrdeo) Ask for free passage.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Excuse me, but I'm Tyrdeo, the President of the Republic. As such, I'm one of the leaders of the Coalition and so I'm politely asking for safe passage."

					The guards tilts their head for a moment before shrugging. "Very well, President. I will let the fleet know at once." The guard also sends some supplies your way.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true" req="FR_LIST_CREW_RUES">
				<text>(R.U.E.S. Elite Crew) Try to persuade them to let you go.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"I see I have been terribly confused. You can't be a Federation ship, not with one of our elite soldiers with you. You may pass." The guard turns their focus back to the rebel forces, but not before sending some supplies to aid you.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="unique_vance" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Vance Prime) Ask for help from the fleet.</text>
				<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_COALITION_VANCE"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_COALITION_VANCE">
	<ship hostile="true"/>
	<text>Vance enters the specific frequency that the local MFK fleet uses to communicate before clearing his throat 
		
	"Soldiers! This is Vance Prime speaking! Any troops avaliable for battle must report immediately and attack the Coalition guard that stands in our way!"

	The Coalition guard bursts out laughting "Oh please! Your troops are being pushed back further by the second, you think they have the manpower to aid you? It's no wonder the Rebellion is dyin-" The Coalition captain stops mid sentence as intruder alarms start blaring down on the enemy ship, it seems the fleet had a few MFK soldiers to spare! That didn't stop the guard from attacking you however.</text>
	<!-- Defector spawned in fr_scripts/Fr_Events.lua -->
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<ship name="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION" auto_blueprint="MU_COALITION_GUARD_ELITE">
	<surrender min="999" max="999" load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_SIGNAL"/>
	<destroyed load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_DESTROY"/>
	<deadCrew load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_DEADCREW"/>
</ship>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_SIGNAL">
	<text>It appears the guard ship is sending out a distress signal to a nearby ASB platform! Brace for impact!</text>
	<choice hidden="true" req="PDS_DISABLE">
		<text>(Signal Diluter) Jam their signal.</text>
		<event>
			<text>When no ASB activates, you assume that is a good sign that your augment has functioned properly, and you continue to fight.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Suddenly you detect a shift in the rebel fleet in the distance, its guns now pointing at the Coalition guard!</text>
			<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
			<noASBPlanet/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_DESTROY">
	<text>You have defeated the Coalition guard. Whatever might have been in their cargo has for certain been destroyed, but you can at least salvage some supplies from the ship.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_FOLLOWUP"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_DEADCREW">
	<text>You have defeated the Coalition guard. Without crew on board to stop you, you can investigate their cargo. You find a weapon to bring back to the ship, and move on to scrap their hull.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<weapon name="GIFTLIST_COALITION"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_FOLLOWUP"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_COALITION_FOLLOWUP">
	<noQuestText/>
	<removeHazards/>
	<text>By killing the Coalition guard, you have no doubt caused them to dispatch reinforcements to track you down. Watch your step as you explore the sector. Though with how chaotic this sector is, there's a chance the forces here will be too busy to deal with you.</text>
	<quest event="FR_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_COALITION">
		<nebulaBeacon>true</nebulaBeacon>
		<nextSector>false</nextSector>
		<nebulaEvent>FR_NEBULA_LIGHT_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_COALITION</nebulaEvent>
		<createNebula>false</createNebula>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="FR_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_COALITION">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>"We will destroy you Federation scum! You will regret ever coming here!" A hostile Elite Coalition ship approaches, and you suspect they're angry for a lot more than just the dead guard.

	However, before the fight can truly start, you detect that the Federation fleet in the distance has also turned its guns on the Coalition ship. It's an all-out brawl now!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_COALITIONHOLD_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
	<noASBPlanet/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_NEBULA_LIGHT_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_COALITION">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>"We will destroy you Federation scum! You will regret ever coming here!" A hostile Elite Coalition ship approaches, and you suspect they're angry for a lot more than just the dead guard.

	However, before the fight can truly start, you detect that the Federation fleet in the distance has also turned its guns on the Coalition ship. It's an all-out brawl now!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_COALITIONHOLD_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_STARS_SPARSE"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
	<noASBPlanet/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>


<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_REBEL">
	<metaVariable name="fr_juke_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<variable name="fr_sec_unique_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_start" global="false">
		<color r="46" g="252" b="51" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>This sector would have once been a safe haven for you and your crew, but ever since the Rebel attack and the sequential Coalition invasion, this sector has become a no man's land. If that wasn't bad enough, pirates have also been drawn into this place hoping to score easy scrap. Watch your step and always be on guard.</text>
	<variable name="loc_unique_sectors" op="add" val="1"/>
	<changeBackground>FR_BACK_SECTOR_WARZONE</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_MFK</customFleet>
	<ship load="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_REBEL" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>It seems the Rebels have managed to hold on to the sector's entrance enough to have an MFK Ace Guard still standing. They notice you right away and power on their weapons and artillery. "Oh, of course a goddamn renegade would stick their nose where it doesn't belong, we are already dealing with enough shit at the moment, the last thing we need is a Federation dog causing us trouble!"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Prepare for combat!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You lock your weapons onto the guard and move in to attack.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="unique_vance" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Vance Prime) "Halt, soldier! Stand down, and allow us to pass!"</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh, shit! Vance Prime! I-I'm sorry for the misunderstanding, we ID'd you as a Fed! We will tell the fleet to help you whenever they can but I'm afraid we have our hands full at the moment, so we can't spare much. If you have the time, please send a few Coalition ships to hell for us!" The MFK Ace guard powers down their weapons before sending an all-clear signal and barely dodging an ASB shot. They then beam aboard an MFK soldier to aid in your journey.</text>
						<crewMember amount="1" class="human_mfk"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="fr_unique_vance_one" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Vance One) "Halt, soldier! Stand down, and allow us to pass!"</text>
				<event>
					<text>The MFK Ace guard blnks before shouting "ONE?! What the hell are you doing here?! I don't care if this will get me court-martialialed; we won't let you pass after everything you have done!"</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true" req="unique_cyra">
				<text>(Cyra) "Halt, brave soldier! This ship is under the command of an MFK Ace! Unpower your weapons immediately!"</text>
				<event>
					<text>The MFK Ace guard is shocked to see Cyra and hastely powers down their weapons and artillery "My mistake ma'am! We are sending all the supplies we can spare as an apology for our brash behaviour!" The guard dispatches a few crates of supplies before turning their attention back to the Coalition fleet.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true" req="human_mfk">
				<text>(MFK Ace Crew) Have the MFK convince them to let you through.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Ah, working undercover are you? Smart, I'm sure whatever mission you were given will be a glorious victory for the Rebellion!" The MFK Ace guard laughs and sends some supplies to aid you before turning their atention back to the invading Coalition.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true" req="LIST_CREW_JERRY">
				<text>(Jerry) "Hello!"</text>
				<event>
					<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY_HELLO"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="true" req="REBEL_ID">
				<text>(Forged Identification) Try to pass your ship for a rebel one.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"You... you really think I would fall for that? Wow..." The MFK Ace guard ends the call and moves in to attack.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="unique_nights" blue="true" hidden="true">
				<text>(Nights) Nights has something to say.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Nights chuckles, taking another swig of his beer. "Tell me...How do you expect to beat ussss without your fancy artillery?" He presses a big red button on a strange remote he carries behind his back.

					"What? What are you talking about, you drunken slug?" The guard asks confused before a giant explosion cuts the call, with Nights cackling drunkely as the enemy's artilery is disabled temporarily.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<enemyDamage amount="3" system="artillery" effect="fire"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>


