	However, before the fight can truly start, you detect that the Federation fleet in the distance has also turned its guns on the rebel ship. It's an all-out brawl now!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_REBELHOLD_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_STARS_SPARSE"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
	<noASBPlanet/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION">
	<metaVariable name="fr_juke_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<variable name="fr_sec_unique_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_start" global="false">
		<color r="46" g="252" b="51" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>This sector would have once been a safe haven for you and your crew, but ever since the Rebel attack and the sequential Coalition invasion, this sector has become a no man's land. If that wasn't bad enough, pirates have also been drawn into this place hoping to score easy scrap. Watch your step and always be on guard.</text>
	<variable name="loc_unique_sectors" op="add" val="1"/>
	<changeBackground>FR_BACK_SECTOR_WARZONE</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES_MFK_MIXED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<ship load="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true" req="rep_comb_federation" lvl="-999" max_lvl="2" max_group="0" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FRIENDLY"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="rep_comb_federation" lvl="3" max_lvl="999" max_group="0" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_CRIMINAL"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FRIENDLY">
	<text>By some miracle the Federation forces in this sector managed to weather the attacks from the Rebels and the Coalition enough to still have a elite guard present. Their weapons power on for a moment before they realize you aren't a threat "I'm sorry, renegade, we have all been on edge since the invasion started. We are short on manpower and ships but we do have a surpluss of weapons, if you are interested of course. Otherwise we can repair or refuel your ship."</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Request support.</text>
		<event load="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FRIENDLY_SUPPORT"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Attack the guard.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The guard's captain is shocked that you've turned on them. "I knew something was fishy about you! We won't let you step any further, you maniac renegade!"</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_GENERAL_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Ignore the guard.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You now have some time to do something on the ship.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FRIENDLY_SUPPORT">
	<text>The guard puts you on a secure line with one of the few surviving nearby support ships, who awaits your command.</text>
	<choice req="unique_tully" hidden="true">
		<text>(Tully) Request support.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The guard looks surprised. "Admiral Tully? What are you doing here?! This is an active warzone! Never mind, we'll give you everything we can possibly spare!"</text>
			<damage amount="-10"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="missiles" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="drones" min="5" max="5"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="unique_turzil" hidden="true">
		<text>(Turzil) Request support.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The guard smiles at seeing the Engi Brigade Leader. "Turzil, it's good to see a friendly face in our time of need. We hope your strategic mind can help us turn the tide of this battle just like it did back in first civil war! We'll give what we can."</text>
			<damage amount="-10"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="missiles" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="drones" min="5" max="5"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="unique_mafan" hidden="true">
		<text>(Mafan) Request support.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It takes the guard a moment to register who is in front of him. "Doctor, you have business in this sector? Please watch your step though, danger lurks around every corner here."</text>
			<damage amount="-10"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="missiles" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="drones" min="5" max="5"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="unique_tyerel" hidden="true">
		<text>(Ty E'rel) Request support.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The guard nods. "Of course, Ambassador. We'll send over whatever you need. I do hope your ship is well equiped however, a silver tongue won't do much good in this place..."</text>
			<damage amount="-10"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="missiles" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="drones" min="5" max="5"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="unique_ruwen" hidden="true">
		<text>(Ruwen) Request support.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The guard nods. "Of course, Ambassador. We'll send over whatever you need. I do hope your ship is well equiped however, a silver tongue won't do much good in this place..."</text>
			<damage amount="-10"/>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="missiles" min="5" max="5"/>
				<item type="drones" min="5" max="5"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Weapon.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A resupply drone is dispatched to resupply your ship with a brand new weapon.</text>
			<weapon name="GIFTLIST_FEDERATION"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Drone.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A resupply drone is dispatched to resupply your ship with a brand new drone.</text>
			<drone name="GIFTLIST_ENGI"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Repairs.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Several repair drones are dispatched to repair you.</text>
			<damage amount="-5"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Fuel.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A refueling drone is dispatched to refuel your ship.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="3" max="3"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ammo.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A resupply drone is dispatched to resupply your ship.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="missiles" min="2" max="2"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Drone parts.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A resupply drone is dispatched to resupply your ship.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="drones" min="2" max="2"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_FEDERATION_CRIMINAL">
	<text>Something seems off here. Usually, the Federation would certainly not bat an eye at a ship like yours, but now, you catch suspicious chatter on the guard ship.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>It seems your track record has caught up to you. The guard's crew have heard enough of the crimes you've been committing, and while they have their hands full at the moment, they can't risk letting you into the sector without a fight!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<ship name="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION" auto_blueprint="MU_FED_GUARD_ELITE">
	<surrender min="999" max="999" load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_SIGNAL"/>
	<destroyed load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_DESTROY"/>
	<deadCrew load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_DEADCREW"/>
</ship>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_SIGNAL">
	<text>It appears the guard ship is sending out a distress signal to a nearby ASB platform! Brace for impact!</text>
	<choice hidden="true" req="PDS_DISABLE">
		<text>(Signal Diluter) Jam their signal.</text>
		<event>
			<text>When no ASB activates, you assume that is a good sign that your augment has functioned properly, and you continue to fight.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Suddenly you detect a shift in the Coalition and MFK fleets in the distance, its guns now pointing at the Federation guard!</text>
			<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
			<noASBPlanet/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_DESTROY">
	<text>You have defeated the Federation guard. Whatever might have been in their cargo has for certain been destroyed, but you can at least salvage some supplies from the ship.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FOLLOWUP"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_DEADCREW">
	<text>You have defeated the Federation guard. Without crew on board to stop you, you can investigate their cargo. You find a weapon to bring back to the ship, and move on to scrap their hull.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<weapon name="GIFTLIST_FEDERATION"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FOLLOWUP"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_FEDERATION_FOLLOWUP">
	<noQuestText/>
	<removeHazards/>
	<text>By killing the Federation guard, you have no doubt caused them to dispatch reinforcements to track you down. Watch your step as you explore the sector. Though with how chaotic this sector is, there's a chance the forces here will be too busy to deal with you.</text>
	<quest event="FR_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_FEDERATION">
		<nebulaBeacon>true</nebulaBeacon>
		<nextSector>false</nextSector>
		<nebulaEvent>FR_NEBULA_LIGHT_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_FEDERATION</nebulaEvent>
		<createNebula>false</createNebula>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_FEDERATION">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>You catch sight of a Federation ship, but they don't seem pleased to see you. "Turncoats! You should be ashamed!" The ship moves in to attack, and it doesn't take long for you to realize this is one of the ships sent by the guards to hunt you down for attacking.
			
	However, before the fight can truly start, you detect that the MFK and Coalition fleets in the distance has also turned its guns on the Federation ship. It's an all-out brawl now!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_FED_UNIQUE_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES_MFK_MIXED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
	<noASBPlanet/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_NEBULA_LIGHT_REINFORCEMENTS_WARZONE_FEDERATION">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>You catch sight of a Federation ship, but they don't seem pleased to see you. "Turncoats! You should be ashamed!" The ship moves in to attack, and it doesn't take long for you to realize this is one of the ships sent by the guards to hunt you down for attacking.
			
	However, before the fight can truly start, you detect that the MFK and Coalition fleets in the distance has also turned its guns on the Federation ship. It's an all-out brawl now!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_FED_UNIQUE_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES_MFK_MIXED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_UNITY</customFleet>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_STARS_SPARSE"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<environment type="PDS" target="all"/>
	<noASBPlanet/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="FR_START_WARZONE_PIRATE">
	<metaVariable name="fr_juke_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<variable name="fr_sec_unique_warzone" op="set" val="1"/>
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_start" global="false">
		<color r="46" g="252" b="51" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text>This sector would have once been a safe haven for you and your crew, but ever since the Rebel attack and the sequential Coalition invasion, this sector has become a no man's land. If that wasn't bad enough, pirates have also been drawn into this place hoping to score easy scrap. Watch your step and always be on guard.</text>
	<variable name="loc_unique_sectors" op="add" val="1"/>
	<changeBackground>FR_BACK_SECTOR_WARZONE</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_RUES_MFK_MIXED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="true">FR_CUSTOM_FLEET_PIRATE</customFleet>
	<ship load="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_PIRATE" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>In a shocking turn of events, a group of pirates has somehow taken over the entry beacon. Whatever Federation resistance there was here has almost certainly been destroyed, leaving the outlaws to be able to let anyone they want to enter. Of course, the Rebels and the Coalition aren't exactly happy with this outcome, and so have been trying their hardest to break through the pirate's fleet.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>The pirate guard soon hails you. On the video screen, a tall, strong woman with scars all over her arms greets you. "Ah, what do we have here, fellas? A Renegade? My, my, that's quite rare around these parts. Still flying that Federation banner, I see? Well, don't keep me from your important little journey. We aren't letting everyone through though. As I'm sure you are well aware, this sector is a bit of a hellzone. Although, if you give us some scrap, that might pull our attention away from this post for a bit." She chuckles menacingly and winks.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Prepare for combat!</text>
						<event>
							<text>You lock your weapons onto the guard and move in to attack.</text>
							<ship hostile="true"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Pay the fee.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Good choice, kid." The pirate nods before shutting off the call, the ship quickly moving to assist on the defense now that you are no longer in their way.</text>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-50" max="-35"/>
							</item_modify>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice req="fr_unique_purple_beard" blue="true" hidden="true">
						<text>(Purple Beard) "Let us pass....Sarah..."</text>
						<event>
							<text>She stares at Purple Beard for a few seconds before chuckling and shaking her head. "Whatever you say, boss. Here, for the road ahead." She winks and transfers over a weapon and some supplies.</text>
							<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
							<autoReward level="MED">standard_no_item</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice req="unique_nights" blue="true" hidden="true">
						<text>(Nights) Nights demands free passage!</text>
						<event>
							<text>"That'ssss where you're misssstaken, bucko. I am Captain Nightssss, and I will be passssing through your checkpoint without paying a ssssingle fragment of ssssscrap. The only quesssstion issss, will I be adding the hull of your sssship to my own richessss? Well? Do we underssstand each other?"

							The guard growls, the ship's weapons powering on "You think I care about a slime like *you*?! You know what, forget the bribe, I want your *head*!"</text>
							<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
							<autoReward level="MED">standard_no_item</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="unique_kaz">
						<text>(Kazaaakplethkilik) Tell them they are in the presence of a legend.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"You are being in the presence of the great Kazaaakplethkilik Tiiikazpakaziiika! If you are not standing down, then your head will hit the floor before you are realizing I am cutting it off!"
							
							The guard gasps. "It... it's an honor. Of course, you may go as you please."
							
							"I am needing some extra scrap for your time. You are giving?"
							
							The guard sighs and meekly nods before giving the legendary pirate what he wants.</text>
							<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="unique_tuco">
						<text>(Tuco) Intimidate the guard.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Hah! You think a greenhorn like you can shake down the likes of me, the Dread Pirate Tuco?"
							
							"The Dread Pirate Tuco??"
							
							"You listen here. Not only may I go freely where I wish, I demand compensation for such an insult!"
							
							"Y-yes, of course, Tuco." The pirate guard dispenses some scrap your way.
							
							"Be seein' you."</text>
							<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_A55">
						<text>(A55) Transmit access code.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Arr, see this code? Do ye know who I am?"
							
							"Captain A55? What business do you have here?"
							
							"Ain't none o' yers! Bein' that I bring many a successful booty to these lands, best step aside, aye?"
							
							"Of course, A55. You can go as you please."
							
							"An' top us off while yer at it!"</text>
							<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="human_angel">
						<text>(Angel Crew) "This ship is empowered by the Syndicate to go where it pleases."</text>
						<event>
							<text>The guard is profusely apologetic. "Of course, please allow us to present you with a tribute. That's a very nice ship that you've taken there."</text>
							<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>


<ship name="FR_SHIP_GUARD_WARZONE_PIRATE" auto_blueprint="FR_LIST_SHIPS_PIRATE_GUARD_ELITE">
	<surrender min="999" max="999" load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_PIRATE_SIGNAL"/>
	<destroyed load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_PIRATE_DESTROY"/>
	<deadCrew load="FR_GUARD_WARZONE_PIRATE_DEADCREW"/>
